            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I've gone back and forth a bit on this - it would avoid a nasty performance issue, but at the cost of a hidden global variable (which is often worth avoiding).\n\nOne additional thought was - it could be a tri-state of \"definitely exception\", \"definitively not exception\" and \"maybe exception\". That provides a way of avoiding the problem with knowing what external modules do - they'd just leave it untouched in the \"maybe\" state and keep working as they do now.",
